name: TreeSet
comment: A quiver/dart-core.Set of items stored in a binary tree according to quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.comparator. Supports bidirectional iteration.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of elements in the iterable.

This is an efficient operation that doesn't require iterating through the elements.

iterator.name: iterator
iterator.comment: Returns an dart-core.BidirectionalIterator that iterates over this tree.

reverseIterator.name: reverseIterator
reverseIterator.comment: Returns an dart-core.BidirectionalIterator that iterates over this tree, in reverse.

constructors.comment: Create a new quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet with an ordering defined by quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.TreeSet-.comparator or the default quiver/dart-core.Comparable.compare.

fromIterator.name: fromIterator
fromIterator.comment:
Returns an dart-core.BidirectionalIterator that starts at quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.fromIterator.anchor. By default, the iterator includes the anchor with the first movement; set quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.fromIterator.inclusive to false if you want to exclude the anchor. Set quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.fromIterator.reversed to true to change the direction of of moveNext and movePrevious.

Note: This iterator allows you to walk the entire set. It does not present a subview.

nearest.name: nearest
nearest.comment: Search the tree for the matching quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.nearest.object or the quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.nearest.nearestOption if missing. See quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSearch.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

iterator.name: iterator
iterator.comment:
Provides an iterator that iterates over the elements of this set.

The order of iteration is defined by the individual Set implementation, but must be consistent between changes to the set.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of elements in the iterable.

This is an efficient operation that doesn't require iterating through the elements.

isEmpty.name: isEmpty
isEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is no element in this collection.

isNotEmpty.name: isNotEmpty
isNotEmpty.comment: Returns true if there is at least one element in this collection.

first.name: first
first.comment:
Returns the first element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError. Otherwise this method is equivalent to this.elementAt(0)

last.name: last
last.comment:
Returns the last element.

If this is empty throws a dart-core.StateError.

single.name: single
single.comment:
Returns the single element in this.

If this is empty or has more than one element throws a dart-core.StateError.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

map.name: map
map.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable where each element e of this is replaced by the result of f(e).

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.map.f will not be invoked. The transformed elements will not be cached. Iterating multiple times over the the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.map.f multiple times on the same element.

where.name: where
where.comment:
Returns a lazy dart-core.Iterable with all elements that satisfy the predicate test.

This method returns a view of the mapped elements. As long as the returned dart-core.Iterable is not iterated over, the supplied function test will not be invoked. Iterating will not cache results, and thus iterating multiple times over the returned dart-core.Iterable will invoke the supplied function test multiple times on the same element.

expand.name: expand
expand.comment:
Expands each element of this dart-core.Iterable into zero or more elements.

The resulting Iterable runs through the elements returned by quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.expand.f for each element of this, in order.

The returned dart-core.Iterable is lazy, and calls quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.expand.f for each element of this every time it's iterated.

contains.name: contains
contains.comment: Returns true if quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.contains.value is in the set.

forEach.name: forEach
forEach.comment: Applies the function quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.forEach.f to each element of this collection.

reduce.name: reduce
reduce.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining elements of the collection using the provided function.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.reduce((value, element) => value + element);

fold.name: fold
fold.comment:
Reduces a collection to a single value by iteratively combining each element of the collection with an existing value using the provided function.

Use quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.fold.initialValue as the initial value, and the function quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.fold.combine to create a new value from the previous one and an element.

Example of calculating the sum of an iterable:

iterable.fold(0, (prev, element) => prev + element);

every.name: every
every.comment: Returns true if every elements of this collection satisify the predicate test. Returns false otherwise.

join.name: join
join.comment:
Converts each element to a dart-core.String and concatenates the strings.

Converts each element to a dart-core.String by calling quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.toString on it. Then concatenates the strings, optionally separated by the quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.join.separator string.

any.name: any
any.comment: Returns true if one element of this collection satisfies the predicate test. Returns false otherwise.

toList.name: toList
toList.comment:
Creates a dart-core.List containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

The elements are in iteration order. The list is fixed-length if quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.toList.growable is false.

toSet.name: toSet
toSet.comment: Creates a dart-core.Set containing the elements of this dart-core.Iterable.

take.name: take
take.comment:
Returns an dart-core.Iterable with at most quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.take.n elements.

The returned dart-core.Iterable may contain fewer than quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.take.n elements, if this contains fewer than quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.take.n elements.

It is an error if quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.take.n is negative.

takeWhile.name: takeWhile
takeWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that stops once quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.takeWhile.test is not satisfied anymore.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable starts iterating over the elements of this.

When the iterator encounters an element e that does not satisfy quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.takeWhile.test, it discards e and moves into the finished state. That is, it does not get or provide any more elements.

skip.name: skip
skip.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips the first quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.skip.n elements.

If this has fewer than quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.skip.n elements, then the resulting Iterable is empty.

It is an error if quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.skip.n is negative.

skipWhile.name: skipWhile
skipWhile.comment:
Returns an Iterable that skips elements while quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.skipWhile.test is satisfied.

The filtering happens lazily. Every new Iterator of the returned Iterable iterates over all elements of this.

As long as the iterator's elements satisfy quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.skipWhile.test they are discarded. Once an element does not satisfy the quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.skipWhile.test the iterator stops testing and uses every later element unconditionally. That is, the elements of the returned Iterable are the elements of this starting from the first element that does not satisfy quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.skipWhile.test.

firstWhere.name: firstWhere
firstWhere.comment:
Returns the first element that satisfies the given predicate quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.firstWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.firstWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.firstWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

lastWhere.name: lastWhere
lastWhere.comment:
Returns the last element that satisfies the given predicate quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.lastWhere.test.

If none matches, the result of invoking the quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.lastWhere.orElse function is returned. By default, when quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.lastWhere.orElse is null, a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

singleWhere.name: singleWhere
singleWhere.comment: Returns the single element that satisfies quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.singleWhere.test. If no or more than one element match then a dart-core.StateError is thrown.

elementAt.name: elementAt
elementAt.comment:
Returns the quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.elementAt.indexth element.

The quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.elementAt.index must be non-negative and less than quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.length.

Note: if this does not have a deterministic iteration order then the function may simply return any element without any iteration if there are at least quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.elementAt.index elements in this.

add.name: add
add.comment:
Adds quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.add.value into the set. Returns true if quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.add.value was added to the set.

If quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.add.value already exists, the set is not changed and false is returned.

addAll.name: addAll
addAll.comment:
Adds all of quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.addAll.elements to this Set.

Equivalent to adding each element in quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.addAll.elements using quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.add, but some collections may be able to optimize it.

remove.name: remove
remove.comment: Removes quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.remove.value from the set. Returns true if quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.remove.value was in the set. Returns false otherwise. The method has no effect if quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.remove.value value was not in the set.

lookup.name: lookup
lookup.comment:
If an object equal to quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.lookup.object is in the set, return it.

Checks if there is an object in the set that is equal to quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.lookup.object. If so, that object is returned, otherwise returns null.

removeAll.name: removeAll
removeAll.comment: Removes each element of quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.removeAll.elements from this set.

retainAll.name: retainAll
retainAll.comment:
Removes all elements of this set that are not elements in quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.retainAll.elements.

Checks for each element of quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.retainAll.elements whether there is an element in this set that is equal to it (according to this.contains), and if so, the equal element in this set is retained, and elements that are not equal to any element in elements are removed.

removeWhere.name: removeWhere
removeWhere.comment: Removes all elements of this set that satisfy quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.removeWhere.test.

retainWhere.name: retainWhere
retainWhere.comment: Removes all elements of this set that fail to satisfy quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.retainWhere.test.

containsAll.name: containsAll
containsAll.comment: Returns whether this Set contains all the elements of quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.containsAll.other.

intersection.name: intersection
intersection.comment:
Returns a new set which is the intersection between this set and quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.intersection.other.

That is, the returned set contains all the elements of this dart-core.Set that are also elements of quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.intersection.other according to other.contains.

union.name: union
union.comment:
Returns a new set which contains all the elements of this set and quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.union.other.

That is, the returned set contains all the elements of this dart-core.Set and all the elements of quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.union.other.

difference.name: difference
difference.comment:
Returns a new set with the the elements of this that are not in quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.difference.other.

That is, the returned set contains all the elements of this dart-core.Set that are not elements of quiver/quiver-collection.TreeSet.difference.other according to other.contains.
